column17:
All of the posts are coordinating a campaign to vote for RM for the SECAwards, which is not related to the topic of the US military. However, one post stands out as using a Distract tactic:

@Haxley17 1899 I vote #RM for #ArtistaAsiatico at #SECAwards

This post brings up a completely irrelevant topic of "1899," which has nothing to do with the SECAwards or voting for RM. This could be an attempt to distract or confuse readers by including a random number. This post does not contribute to the coordinated campaign for voting for RM in the SECAwards and instead veers off into a different, unrelated topic.
